      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>How I enjoyed Melissa Clark's article celebrating grilled cheese (''Taking Back a Childhood Favorite,'' April 11).</p>
        <p>As a 20-something bachelor living alone, grilled cheese is perfect for fulfilling that need for an easy-to-make, end-of-a-long-day comfort food.</p>
        <p>Based on my extensive experience, a suggestion: use olive oil instead of butter. It gives the sandwich a lighter, more sophisticated taste, works just as well and, of course, is much healthier. My personal favorite: honey wheat bread, Muenster cheese, tomato slices, topped with spicy mustard. Amazing!</p>
        <p>Ari Gerstman  Alexandria, Va.</p>
      </block>
